--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Kasai v2.0.0 *very* short installation guide
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To use Kasai within your application:
-------------------------------------

1) Create the database structure:

$ mysql -p -u <username> <database name> < kasai.sql

2) Add kasai-2.0.x.jar to your CLASSPATH

3) Add the org.manentia.kasai.Config properties file to your CLASSPATH (org/manentia/kasai/Config.properties).

4) Edit the Config.properties file to match your environment

See the QuickStart Guide for detailed instructions and examples. 
Get it at http://kasai.manentiasoftware.com

To install Kasai bundled web administrative tool:
-------------------------------------------------

1) Create the database structure (if you didn't already):

$ mysql -p -u <username> <database name> < kasai.sql

2) Add the Config.properties and Messages.properties files to your Servlet container CLASSPATH, within the org.manentia.kasai package. 
For example to do this in Tomcat 5.x you can copy both files to <tomcat>/shared/classes/org/manentia/kasai/.

3) Edit the Config.properties file to match your environment

4) Deploy the web application (kasai.war). In most servlet containers you can do this by copying the WAR file to some pre-defined location (ie <tomcat>/webapps) or by defining a new context that points to it.

5) If needed restart your servlet container